$t = array();
$t[1] = 'Qaf: By the Glorious Qur\'an (Thou art Allah\'s Messenger).';
$t[2] = 'But they wonder that there has come to them a Warner from among themselves. So the Unbelievers say: &quot;This is a wonderful thing!';
$t[3] = '&quot;What! When we die and become dust, (shall we live again?) That is a (sort of) return far (from our understanding).&quot;';
$t[4] = 'We already know how much of them the earth takes away: With Us is a record guarding (the full account).';
$t[5] = 'But they deny the Truth when it comes to them: so they are in a confused state.';
$t[6] = 'Do they not look at the sky above them?- How We have made it and adorned it, and there are no flaws in it?';
$t[7] = 'And the earth- We have spread it out, and set thereon mountains standing firm, and produced therein every kind of beautiful growth (in pairs)-';
$t[8] = 'To be observed and commemorated by every devotee turning (to Allah).';
$t[9] = 'And We send down from the sky rain charted with blessing, and We produce therewith gardens and Grain for harvests;';
$t[10] = 'And tall (and stately) palm-trees, with shoots of fruit-stalks, piled one over another;-';
$t[11] = 'As sustenance for (Allah\'s) Servants;- and We give (new) life therewith to land that is dead: Thus will be the Resurrection.';
$t[12] = 'Before them was denied (the Hereafter) by the People of Noah, the Companions of the Rass, the Thamud,';
$t[13] = 'The \'Ad, Pharaoh, the brethren of Lut,';
$t[14] = 'The Companions of the Wood, and the People of Tubba\'; each one (of them) rejected the messengers, and My warning was duly fulfilled (in them).';
$t[15] = 'Were We then weary with the first Creation, that they should be in confused doubt about a new Creation?';
$t[16] = 'It was We Who created man, and We know what dark suggestions his soul makes to him: for We are nearer to him than (his) jugular vein.';
$t[17] = 'Behold, two (guardian angels) appointed to learn (his doings) learn (and noted them), one sitting on the right and one on the left.';
$t[18] = 'Not a word does he utter but there is a sentinel by him, ready (to note it).';
$t[19] = 'And the stupor of death will bring Truth (before his eyes): &quot;This was the thing which thou wast trying to escape!&quot;';
$t[20] = 'And the Trumpet shall be blown: that will be the Day whereof Warning (had been given).';
$t[21] = 'And there will come forth every soul: with each will be an (angel) to drive, and an (angel) to bear witness.';
$t[22] = '(It will be said:) &quot;Thou wast heedless of this; now have We removed thy veil, and sharp is thy sight this Day!&quot;';
$t[23] = 'And his Companion will say: &quot;Here is (his Record) ready with me!&quot;';
$t[24] = '(The sentence will be:) &quot;Throw, throw into Hell every contumacious Rejecter (of Allah)!-';
$t[25] = '&quot;Who forbade what was good, transgressed all bounds, cast doubts and suspicions;';
$t[26] = '&quot;Who set up another god beside Allah: Throw him into a severe penalty.&quot;';
$t[27] = 'His Companion will say: &quot;Our Lord! I did not make him transgress, but he was (himself) far astray.&quot;';
$t[28] = 'He will say: &quot;Dispute not with each other in My Presence: I had already in advance sent you Warning.';
$t[29] = '&quot;The Word changes not before Me, and I do not the least injustice to My Servants.&quot;';
$t[30] = 'One Day We will ask Hell, &quot;Art thou filled to the full?&quot; It will say, &quot;Are there any more (to come)?&quot;';
$t[31] = 'And the Garden will be brought nigh to the Righteous,- no more a thing distant.';
$t[32] = '(A voice will say:) &quot;This is what was promised for you,- for every one who turned (to Allah) in sincere repentance, who kept (His Law),';
$t[33] = '&quot;Who feared (Allah) Most Gracious Unseen, and brought a heart turned in devotion (to Him):';
$t[34] = '&quot;Enter ye therein in Peace and Security; this is a Day of Eternal Life!&quot;';
$t[35] = 'There will be for them therein all that they wish,- and more besides in Our Presence.';
$t[36] = 'But how many generations before them did We destroy (for their sins),- stronger in power than they? Then did they wander through the land: was there any place of escape (for them)?';
$t[37] = 'Verily in this is a Message for any that has a heart and understanding or who gives ear and earnestly witnesses (the truth).';
$t[38] = 'We created the heavens and the earth and all between them in Six Days, nor did any sense of weariness touch Us.';
$t[39] = 'Bear, then, with patience, all that they say, and celebrate the praises of thy Lord, before the rising of the sun and before (its) setting.';
$t[40] = 'And during part of the night, (also,) celebrate His praises, and (so likewise) after the postures of adoration.';
$t[41] = 'And listen for the Day when the Caller will call out from a place quiet near,-';
$t[42] = 'The Day when they will hear a (mighty) Blast in (very) truth: that will be the Day of Resurrection.';
$t[43] = 'Verily it is We Who give Life and Death; and to Us is the Final Goal-';
$t[44] = 'The Day when the Earth will be rent asunder, from (men) hurrying out: that will be a gathering together,- quite easy for Us.';
$t[45] = 'We know best what they say; and thou art not one to overawe them by force. So admonish with the Qur\'an such as fear My Warning!';
?>